The paper deals with predicting search targets from human fixations on natural images, which is a problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also proposes a new problem formulation for search target prediction, which involves learning compatibilities between fixations and potential targets, indicating a machine learning (cs.LG) aspect. The paper also mentions the use of information retrieval techniques (cs.IR) to retrieve relevant images for the search task. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (cs.CL) to some extent, as it discusses the use of textual descriptions of the search targets.
